                // If `n_stairs_val` is `(1LL << 31) - 1`, then `n_stairs_val + 1` is `1LL << 31`.
                // `2 * n_stairs_val + 1` is `(1LL << 32) - 1`.
                // Next cost is `((1LL << 32) - 1) * (1LL << 31)`. This is `(2^32 - 1) * 2^31`.
                // This is `(2^63 - 2^31)`. This fits in `long long`.
                // If `n_stairs_val` is `(1LL << 32) - 1`, then `n_stairs_val + 1` is `1LL << 32`.
                // `2 * n_stairs_val + 1` is `(1LL << 33) - 1`.
                // Next cost is `((1LL << 33) - 1) * (1LL << 32)`. This is `(2^65 - 2^32)`. This overflows `long long`.
                // So, if `n_stairs_val` is `(1LL << 32) - 1`, we must stop.
